The paper deals with the problem of distinguishing between two or more Hidden Markov Chains (HMCs) based on a single observation sequence. This problem is relevant in various fields such as speech recognition, signal processing, and biological sequence analysis, which are covered by sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
